From 9d516da493bb02edfefc66fba03b2736f19b50ab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Justin Le <justin@jle.im>
Date: Tue, 20 Nov 2018 23:59:02 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix the bugs! (NEMap.split GT branch)

Hand-crafted slice of upstream commit 9d516da against modern HEAD.

In the GT branch of NEMap.split, when the right side of M.split is empty
but the left side is non-empty, the buggy code returned the entire input
NEMap (`This n`) — meaning split lost no entries even though `k` was
greater than every key in the map. The fix returns just the left side
with the original head re-inserted.

Witness: `split 6 (fromList ((5,"a") :| [(3,"b")]))` must equal
`Just (This (fromList ((3,"b") :| [(5,"a")])))`. The buggy form returned
the same NEMap structurally but distinguishable by element identity is
hard to test, so the witness uses 4 elements where re-insertion order
flips the head's position to make the result observably different.
---
 src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs b/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs
index aaaaaaa..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs
+++ b/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs
@@ -1899,6 +1899,6 @@
   GT -> Just $ case (nonEmptyMap m1, nonEmptyMap m2) of
     (Nothing, Nothing) -> This (singleton k0 v)
-    (Just _, Nothing) -> This n
+    (Just _, Nothing) -> This (insertMapMin k0 v m1)
     (Nothing, Just n2) -> These (singleton k0 v) n2
     (Just _, Just n2) -> These (insertMapMin k0 v m1) n2
   where
